               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361024-name-982" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361024-name-982" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361024-name-982" type="surname" value="BASCOMBE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361024-name-982" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE BASCOMBE</persName>
                  </hi>. I was servant to the Hon. Berkeley Paget. On the 17th of October I had this spoon safe in the pantry—on the 19th I was about to leave my situation, and was going to give up my inventory, and could not find this spoon—the prisoner was employed by a person who took the wash away.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361024-name-983" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361024-name-983" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361024-name-983" type="surname" value="ROBINSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361024-name-983" type="given" value="JOHN AUSTIN"></interp>JOHN AUSTIN ROBINSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a silversmith and watchmaker—I live at Kingston-on-Thomas—the Hon. Berkeley Paget lives at Hampton-court. The prisoner tendered this spoon at my shop for sale on he 20th. of October, and the crest being partly obliterated, I asked him some ques<lb></lb>tions—I then gave him and his brother, who came with him, into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
